{
  "stem": "19198.3",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 233.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And another aspect of the welcome was that they all were very, very curious of-- about our experience in Nazi Germany.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "The most important element of the day was our being invited to the office of Dr.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Morgenstern, the president of the school, who formally welcomed us, told us that the entire community was excited about the arrival of these five people, that he-- they want us to feel as welcome as-- as possible, even though, of course, he anticipated that we would have some difficulty with the language, that we had a lot to learn about the-- the way of-- of studying in America in-- and in English.",
      "word_count": 72
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "He assured us that we-- as far as religious practices are concerned, that of course American Reform was more radical than what we were used to in Germany, but that if we felt more at home wearing a head covering, that we should feel free to do so, even though in American Reform that was not the custom.",
      "word_count": 58
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "This caused us some problem later.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Even though it was a very minor problem, I think it is well worth telling the story.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Part of our experience was to be invited into many Jewish homes and Jewish institutions.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "So one Sabbath morning, we, the five of us, went to the Rockdale Avenue Temple in Cincinnati for the Sabbath morning service.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "By that time we knew to anticipate a service which was almost entirely in English.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "We also knew that Dr.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Phillipson was the oldest surviving-- Dr.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Phillipson, the-- who was the senior rabbi of that congregation, was the oldest surviving graduate of the first class of the Hebrew Union College.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "He had been ordained in 1881, or '82.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "At any rate, it was a Classical Reform congregation.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So soon after that, Dr.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
